<figureCitation id="134F2A2A2064FFB4FB928516FB3B4E22" box="[1072,1158,1087,1111]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURES 3–15" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1962,1986]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1722,1746]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,264,1785,1809]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1431,275,1920]" captionTargetBox-1="[164,1426,191,1679]" captionTargetBox-2="[181,1408,201,1744]" captionTargetId-0="figure-83@2.[151,1435,270,1936]" captionTargetId-1="figure-20@3.[151,1436,179,1696]" captionTargetId-2="figure-28@6.[177,1411,181,1761]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Wing venation. Fig. 1a. Hydria cervinalis; Fig. 1b. Rheumaptera hastate. Pay attention to the presence of two areoles in forewing of Hydria vs. one areole in forewing of Rheumaptera." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Terminology of male and female genitalia used in this paper. Fig. 2a, genitalia capsule; Fig. 2b, aedeagus, Fig. 2c, female genitalia, Fig. 2d, last abdominal segments (sternite- and tergite-A7 and A8).Abbreviations as follows (after Schmidt 2017): ant.a.—anterior apophysis, a.p.c.—anterior part of corpus bursae, cor—cornuti, duc—ductus bursae, jux—juxta, lab— labides, lat.l.—lateral lobe, ovi—ovipositor, p.p.c.—posterior part of corpus bursae, pos.a.—posterior apophysis, sac—sacculus projection, sig—signum, St.-A7—sternum A7, St.-A8—sternum A8; unc—uncus, val—valva, ves—vesica, (Photos of Hydria cervinalis)." captionText-2="FIGURES 3–15. Wing pattern. Figs 3–8: Hydria cervinalis cervinalis: Fig. 3, ♂, Germany, Sachsen-Anhalt, Mansfeld; Fig. 4, ♂, Ungarn, prov. Vesprérn, Zsofiapuszta; Fig. 5, ♂, Germany, Ug. Freyburg Zscheiplitz, Schafberg; Fig. 6, ♂, Germany, Umg. Jena; Figs 7 and 8, ♂, Germany, Sachsen-Anhalt, Mansfeld; Figs 9–10: H. cervinalis taurica ssp. n., Turkey, prov. Antalya, Civizli W Seydisehir, Fig. 9, Holotype ♂, (g. prep. DS-120/2012); Fig. 10, Paratype ♀, (g. prep. DS-121/2012); Figs 11–12: H. gernoti sp. n., Turkey, prov. Nigde, Ala Dagi: Fig. 11, Holotype ♂; Fig. 12, Paratype ♀; Figs 13–15: H. schachti sp. n.: Fig. 13, Holotype ♂, Turkey, prov. Erzurum, Meschit Daglari; Fig. 14, Paratype ♀, Turkey, prov. Erzurum, Meschit Daglari; Fig. 15, Paratype ♂, Turkey, prov. Erzurum, Karadeniz Daglari, Korga Dari. a = upperside; b = underside." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5896495" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5896497" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5896501" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5896495/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5896497/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5896501/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="515">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
(
